The general rule is that cross-border transfer is prohibited, unless a foreign state provides an appropriate level of protection of the personal data subjectsâ€™ rights. NPDPC has established that the list of foreign states, which ensure appropriate level of protection. The list includes foreign states that are parties to the Council of Europe Convention for the Protection of Individuals with regard to Automatic Processing of Personal Data, adopted in Strasbourg on 28&nbsp;January&nbsp;1981.
However there are certain exceptions, when transfer to the jurisdictions with inappropriate level of protection will be allowed. For example, upon respective consent of the personal data subject and informing of the possible risks or under the individual permit for cross-border transfer issued by NPDPC.Last modified 21 Feb 2022
				
			